<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="337" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[843,1494,1181,1468]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis box="[889,1160,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[1195,1416,1181,1205]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis box="[1195,1416,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Benstonea pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the montane rainforests (
<quantity box="[1143,1279,1213,1237]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" unit="m" value="1700.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="900.0">900-2500 m</quantity>
) of Borneo and has been collected twice in 
<collectingRegion box="[1095,1184,1245,1269]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[1199,1348,1245,1269]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" pagination="69 - 74" refId="ref16327" refString="STONE, B. C. (1975 a). Studies in Malesian Pandanaceae XV. Two new species of Pandanus from Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah (Borneo) and notes on the Pandanaceae of Mt. Kinabalu. Malay. J. Sci. 3: 69 - 74." type="journal article" year="1975" yearSuffix="a">STONE, 1975a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[1359,1416,1245,1269]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="337" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[843,1494,1181,1468]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis box="[889,1040,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Observations</emphasis>
. – This species is strictly epiphytic and easily distinguished from other epiphytic members of the genus (e.g. 
<taxonomicName box="[974,1092,1348,1372]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alticola">
<emphasis box="[974,1092,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">B. alticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by its lobed auricles at the base of the leaves. 
<taxonomicName box="[966,1188,1380,1404]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pectinata">
<emphasis box="[966,1188,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Benstonea pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been collected on fallen trees in montane rainforests, but seems to be a strict epiphyte (
<figureCitation box="[954,1040,1444,1468]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[103,129,1870,1890]" captionTargetBox="[102,1479,279,1835]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. – Infructescences and details of stigmas of species of Benstonea Callm. &amp; Buerki. A. Benstonea parva (Ridl.) Callm. &amp; Buerki; B. Benstonea pectinata (Martelli) Callm. &amp; Buerki; C. Benstonea rupestris (. C. Stone) Callm. &amp; Buerki; D. Benstonea thomissophylla (. C. Stone) Callm. &amp; Buerki. [Photos: M. W. Callmander]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5790012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5790012/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
